11 SUBTITLE 4C. HOME HEALTH CARE PROVIDER DIRECTORY.
12 19–4C–01.
13 IN THIS SUBTITLE, “HOME HEALTH CARE PROVIDER” MEANS AN INDIVIDUAL
14 WHO PROVIDES HOME HEALTH CARE, AS DEFINED IN § 19–4A–01 OF THIS TITLE,
15 REGARDLESS OF WHETHER THE INDIVIDUAL IS EMPLOYED BY OR CONTRACTS WITH
16 A RESIDENTIAL SERVICE AGENCY.
17 19–4C–02.
18 (A) (1) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL ESTABLISH AND MAINTAIN AN ONLINE
19 DIRECTORY OF EACH HOME CARE PROVIDER IN THE STATE.
20 (2) THE DEPARTMENT SHALL MODEL THE DIRECTORY ON EXISTING
21 DIRECTORIES.
22 (B) THE ONLINE DIRECTORY SHALL ALLOW AN INDIVIDUAL SEEKING HOME
23 HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO SEARCH THE INFORMATION IN THE DIRECTORY AND
24 IDENTIFY A HOME HEALTH CARE PROVIDER BASED ON SPECIFIED CRITERIA, SUCH
25 AS LANGUAGE PROFICIENCY, CERTIFICATIONS, PREVIOUS EXPERIENCE, OR
26 SPECIAL SKILLS.
27 (C) THE DIRECTORY MAY INCLUDE FUNCTIONALITIES THAT:
28 (1) CONNECT AN INDIVIDUAL SEEKING HOME– AND
29 COMMUNITY–BASED SERVICES WITH A QUALIFIED PROVIDER BY:

